</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="FA832407A00C64483CA39302780FA3FA" doi="10.3897/zse.98.82649.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/680586" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" start="Figure 7" startId="F7">
<paragraph id="2168BDD9B23DDA6C8352AABFA9356057" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis id="F9C0B42920B03F82B376D62411953572" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Figure 7.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="A3F90A2B33DC7A4DE6D954B97C9E9C3C" authorityName="Framenau &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2022" family="Araneidae" genus="Mangrovia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mangrovia occidentalis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis id="ED5C1185A560F2C6642F5AC1338E511A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Mangrovia occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., expanded right left pedipalp (WAM T77397). 
<emphasis id="B8BB913A16C7B6002E8CEECCB5D7FC49" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">A.</emphasis>
Apico-dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="3ABD18F2F11763872369CA698A130BA5" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">B.</emphasis>
Mesal view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (
<emphasis id="13FD1DDBE0827A1A2C3CA45DB63FB76E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">A, B</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="70BC408F1551D900824F0C83C12DD7F5" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis id="467CDB9B91DCD8EF9BA2713169C64497" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Female</emphasis>
(based on WAM T75326): Total length 10.8. Carapace (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="385923A450D76167AD679383AC3DEA32" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Mangrovia occidentalis sp. nov., female (WAM T 75326). A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Habitus, ventral view; C. Epigyne, ventral view; D. Epigyne, lateral view; E. Epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.82649.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/680587" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">8A</figureCitation>
) 3.8 long, 3.6 wide; pear-shaped, uniformly reddish-brown; few white setae. Eyes diameter AME 0.25, ALE 0.16, PME 0.18, PLE 0.16; row of eyes: AME 0.65, PME 0.47, PLE 1.64. Chelicerae reddish-brown; four promarginal teeth, second basal largest; three retromarginal teeth of similar size. Legs (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="09FD5F28AB62F7DD1E0FAB1EA6816C35" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Mangrovia occidentalis sp. nov., female (WAM T 75326). A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Habitus, ventral view; C. Epigyne, ventral view; D. Epigyne, lateral view; E. Epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.82649.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/680587" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">8A, B</figureCitation>
) reddish-brown. Pedipalp length (femur + patella + tibia + tarsus = total length): 1.2 + 0.6 + 0.9 + 1.5 = 4.2. Leg formula I&gt; IV&gt; II&gt; III; length of segments (femur + patella + tibia + metatarsus + tarsus = total length): I - 4.6 + 2.1 + 3.5 + 3.4 + 1.1 = 14.7, II - 4.0 + 1.8 + 3.1 + 0.9 + 1.0 = 10.8, III - 2.5 + 1.2 + 1.5 + 1.6 + 0.8 = 7.6, IV - 3.8 + 1.6 + 2.3 + 2.9 + 0.9 = 11.5. Labium and endites reddish-browns. Sternum (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="96CDD1FEE05F7F79A1D0E0B149584E37" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Mangrovia occidentalis sp. nov., female (WAM T 75326). A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Habitus, ventral view; C. Epigyne, ventral view; D. Epigyne, lateral view; E. Epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.82649.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/680587" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">8B</figureCitation>
) heart-shaped, reddish-brown with two small lighter patches along the median line. Abdomen (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="21E3539743EA7A7EFE1BDC5244C1F7DD" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Mangrovia occidentalis sp. nov., female (WAM T 75326). A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Habitus, ventral view; C. Epigyne, ventral view; D. Epigyne, lateral view; E. Epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.82649.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/680587" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">8A, B</figureCitation>
) 6.5 long, 6.3 wide; dorsally beige, with a black band along anterior margin; four pairs of dark brown sigillae; venter olive-brown, with transverse guanine band posterior of epigastric furrow, somewhat lighter anterior of spinnerets and two small white spot antero-lateral of spinnerets. Epigyne (Figs 
<figureCitation id="03CCE1B7CF085278B732CCAF6F852760" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Mangrovia albida comb. nov. (AM KS. 98754) and M. occidentalis sp. nov. (WAM T 75326), cleared female epigynes, posterior view. A. Mangrovia albida comb. nov.; B. M. occidentalis sp. nov. Scale bar: 0.2 mm (A, B)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.82649.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/680583" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">4B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="E1EB81B9F55D4570E37717EFF16FDD06" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Mangrovia occidentalis sp. nov., female (WAM T 75326). A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Habitus, ventral view; C. Epigyne, ventral view; D. Epigyne, lateral view; E. Epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.82649.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/680587" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">8C-E</figureCitation>
) almost twice as wide as long, copulatory openings laterally of scape; scape almost twice as long as epigyne plate, narrow, basally and apically wider, and with terminal pocket. Spermathecae ovoid; fertilisation ducts basally convoluted and attaching posteriorly to spermathecae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C3C9AF9B2410F78EE3C47C42D03C00D6" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Mangrovia albida comb. nov. (AM KS. 98754) and M. occidentalis sp. nov. (WAM T 75326), cleared female epigynes, posterior view. A. Mangrovia albida comb. nov.; B. M. occidentalis sp. nov. Scale bar: 0.2 mm (A, B)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.82649.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/680583" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">4B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="96848C657F8A994ED7B31B03B2C87134" doi="10.3897/zse.98.82649.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/680587" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" start="Figure 8" startId="F8">
<paragraph id="50E0ACB739D8B96138EADF30E5FC54F2" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis id="32FCB0EA87A7E4F36DF5F1D60F01B6EF" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Figure 8.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="E3B7B631C5A1BFEB4BD160B1C8193E5B" authorityName="Framenau &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2022" family="Araneidae" genus="Mangrovia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mangrovia occidentalis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis id="A7F0877BE2BED571049FEE1B7E7665F9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Mangrovia occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., female (WAM T75326). 
<emphasis id="49A2A370DF4A58F2110B67CAF809E060" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">A.</emphasis>
Habitus, dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="8413766B5D4E5A65102D1B897068356D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">B.</emphasis>
Habitus, ventral view; 
