</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6AF8BC25A30D4A785AA0A98412EA7EF5" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" type="variation">
<paragraph id="A260415B8036087838821CF49A58996F" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Variation.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ADF48A2E850FECBA5E4C98015A8E5A90" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Male only known from holotype; the spine on the median apophysis of the left pedipalp was broken off, therefore the right pedipalp is illustrated here. Female total length 8.7-10.6 (n = 8); there was little colour variation in females although the abdomen venter showed distinct white guanine spots in most specimens.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3708960A5E36CBBFBFB31CC6954670C4" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" type="habitat">
<paragraph id="1E4714B23269B0376844913AB7FA255E" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Habitat preferences and life history.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CED50D4EB3239B4754778AD8721C2C32" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">
Collection data on labels with museum specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="43D7C13CC905A76F26A4400AECDD3CC8" genus="M." lsidName="M. occidentalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis id="49F5E89489B0EF22F06A1AF4847F67E8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">M. occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. exclusively lists 
<normalizedToken id="267BB035C32A58685A24016EE66809C7" originalValue="‘mangroves’">'mangroves'</normalizedToken>
as habitat, where, similar to 
<taxonomicName id="E4E70531C18BA57E8F6760EA4EE13076" genus="M." lsidName="M. albida" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="albida">
<emphasis id="1CE530D7DEE190999C67698745A613B5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">M. albida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov., spiders were collected mainly from rolled leaves near the orb-web. Mature spiders were mainly collected in May, July and September with a single record in February.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9CF2BF9B95E3F170985BB947034A32B5" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="F57BE3CC822600871B36A3BCCA4C537D" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5664230D2914E7F6D6E6C331AEAA0BAD" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">
This species is only known from coastal Western Australia (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EF667F972C30D62AC07CE91B9B032505" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Distribution records of Mangrovia occidentalis sp. nov." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.82649.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/680588" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">9</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="2131D339B1EC8C4227E1A4FF7ACD2022" doi="10.3897/zse.98.82649.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/680588" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" start="Figure 9" startId="F9">
